  Locus:
    Page: 19
    Verse: 13
Tags:
  - Anger
---
Anger burns up all that is noble. It is a consuming fire, born of the fires
of destruction. At the end, it leaves the victim nothing but a wreck of his
better self, burned out, blackened and dead, like forest trees over which a
great fire has swept.
